commentary: Ehsan Adil to Stirling, OUT he has played across the line. What a big mistake. Loses patience. Given. He is on the middle-and-off line, Adil stays on that length and within the stumps, Stirling goes across the line, presenting only half the bat, and is beaten. Hit in front. commentary: Rahat Ali to Joyce, no run Rahat gets the wicket. He doesn't? At least according to the umpire, he doesn't, but Pakistan have reviewed it. Umpire RSA Palliyaguruge seems to have made a very good decision. This is on a length, outside off, Joyce opens his face, their is a clear noise as the ball passes the bat. Everybody is sure he is out, but not the umpire. The replays show no clear contact between bat and ball. The snicko registers a disturbance, but a moment before the ball reaches the bat. This is a superb decision, ump, because it sounds out live time

commentary: Wahab Riaz to Joyce, OUT Wahab produces the breakthrough for Pakistan. He just has the knack. Joyce looks to pull from outside off, the ball gets a touch big on him, and he is late into the shot. The top edge lobs up towards short square cover, and Umar Akmal doesn't drop it. Wahab's deceptive pace does it

commentary: Haris Sohail to Balbirnie, OUT oh what a soft dismissal, and against the run of play. That misfield has proved to be a work for genius. Balbirnie stays on strike thanks to that misfield and plays this poor sweep. He hasn't really gone down on this length ball outside off, gets a massive top edge that Afridi takes at short fine leg. He also has to fetch this from well outside off. Premeditated

commentary: Rahat Ali to Porterfield, 2 runs he has dropped him on 99. Driven on the up, fails to keep it down, but it bursts through Rahat's hands. Comes back for two. Removes his helmet to celebrate. KOB leads the applause from the dressing room. Sarfraz claps too. Good spirit out there. It hasn't burst through. Rahat has attempted a catch at the wrong line. Gets hit on the low finger, and the ricochet nearly runs Wilson out, who is backing up

commentary: Sohail Khan to Porterfield, OUT this could just be his last game, but Afridi is doing his best to make sure he isn't. Porterfield looks to drive over mid-on but mistimes. The length ball just gets a little big on him, and lobs off the high part of the bat. Afridi rushes in from the edge of the circle and takes a low diving catch to his left. Porterifeld out for 107. His seventh score between 100 and 112

commentary: Sohail Khan to Wilson, no run Lovely inswinging yorker, given out lbw but Wilson has reviewed it immediately. This has dipped and swung in late, and has hit him in front, but Wilson has got a big inside edge. Marais Erasmus reverses his own decision. It looked out live time. This is a perfect endorsement of DRS

commentary: Sohail Khan to Wilson, OUT bouncer, he looks to upper-cut it, Wilson is off his feet in trying to do so, still can't reach it, and gets a soft top edge on it. This could have been a wide had he not hit, but is only the second bouncer of the over so it can't be called a no-ball
